<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-CA2C7C30-7C47-4FBD-86DB-5FB1F585A8D8" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-CA2C7C30-7C47-4FBD-86DB-5FB1F585A8D8" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">15 How to remove the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">X motion system buffer left encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 15B9 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">XMS_BUF_LEFT_ENC</compsignal></comp> or <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">X motion system buffer right encoder</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 15B10 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">XMS_BUF_RIGHT_ENC</compsignal></comp></title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-AB1FF3F2-EE56-418A-9E2C-98169E865A32" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the buffer plate. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="15DISA012" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-6CDAF753-CB53-4DEF-97F6-A4754B593FB7.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to remove the buffer plate?>15 How to remove the buffer plate</xref> . 
</p></li></ol><note id="GUID-94DCDC88-BB8D-4E80-AB72-5914F3D502D9" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">After removal the old sensor is broken. A new sensor must be installed. 
</p></note></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A32A562039FB485780CA65B069EE577C" class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A new sensor. 
</p></li><li id="LI_1D9EE245DE6547E09D8CB22E45CFC7A0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T10. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li><li id="LI_65FC2CCF351049A499AB816911558F9A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Small screwdriver. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Compressed air. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">The encoder is located above the pulley on both left and right hand side.</title><image href="GUID-95D54B6F-EE2B-4750-8C69-DE61E58BCF5B-low.png" id="IMAGE_CB83DCE3A3444363B328DECF1AC3A58F" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-95D54B6F-EE2B-4750-8C69-DE61E58BCF5B-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_6BEA0AA2C5344ADC8CBE547203C5ED23" class="- topic/fig "><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">The two parts of the sensor: left part = base plate and right part = housing 
</p></desc><image href="GUID-B54E876D-E8F2-4C4D-9042-4B65BAAAA4F2-low.png" id="IMAGE_30E05D8D04554CDDAFFF24513DF04220" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B54E876D-E8F2-4C4D-9042-4B65BAAAA4F2-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_C5F64D1EDF374EEFB875A1A706F76154" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_140E4716CCCB45BFB1AD95964307A25A" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The sensor is mounted using a bayonet locking mechanism. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Looking from above rotate the top part of the sensor counter clock wise. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Approximately 3 mm. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_5D6E4A6544444A23837FAF80731E6985" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1EBF7C32-40DF-409B-8392-4CACAE558253-low.png" id="IMAGE_D387ED2BC26C4915AF46BD86AFB5FD82" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1EBF7C32-40DF-409B-8392-4CACAE558253-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Lift the top part of the sensor off. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The base plate of the encoder must remain on the motor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The base plate is positioned during production and must not be loosened. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If parts of the upper part remain stuck they must be removed by hand. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_4A7FF1BFB1C34E809B48C816D7E829BE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9C024E0F-6F0D-4021-85B4-EF845A2FCF82-low.png" id="IMAGE_F4B40AAB14584DEEA09A912A16089DFD" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9C024E0F-6F0D-4021-85B4-EF845A2FCF82-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connector. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_5E58AE9CBC33463BAD36B1E98547BAFD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-593956CE-E9FD-4682-B111-C1F26C09F841-low.png" id="IMAGE_CE67658387384C61B990BC8120EF753E" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-593956CE-E9FD-4682-B111-C1F26C09F841-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-446EE778-8D2B-4CCF-8B9C-D5D1DB4CCCF4" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to clean the encoder (only required in rare cases)</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-3D59D944-F81E-4AA0-A852-586799D735DC" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the 2 loose parts from the encoder housing by gently pulling the black and white part out. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-18D7FB62-1076-4E5C-A0BB-107AD594F836" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A10565A2-5499-45B5-909E-2D0EDD2A2973-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A10565A2-5499-45B5-909E-2D0EDD2A2973-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Clean the encoder pulse disc and inner housing with compressed air. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Mount the cleaned parts in the encoder housing again. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C2210905-BB37-4182-B96A-735C3F4EE95F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-25E8C3DF-C332-45B1-BFD6-BD47E231385E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-25E8C3DF-C332-45B1-BFD6-BD47E231385E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_A7B7F2276EC64F88A303AD9C9A521E96" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You must only install the top part of the sensor since the bottom part stays on the axis. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you keep the sensor straight when installing. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> During this action the axis must be supported to prevent sliding down when pressing the encoder housing. 
</p><note id="GUID-16D26192-AD47-452C-A592-423F0E167DEC" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> If the axis is not supported, the encoder might not be positioned correctly. After turning the 3 mm counter clockwise the internal play might not be enough. This will have long term wear effects that cannot be verified directly. 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-AAFB5F3D-19D8-445A-AB96-479E596873C4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BF4AD84A-C8A1-4B5A-BB0A-F753EEAABA4D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF4AD84A-C8A1-4B5A-BB0A-F753EEAABA4D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-027A0565-F050-4419-9B19-C5C075964C5A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>